! conclusion: Structured PSR/PUR events parse reliably; free-text does not.
  + context: Realtime matchers depend on consistent schemas and keys.
  + IF:
    PSR/PUR are emitted as free-text or inconsistent key names.
  + HOWEVER:
    Humans may annotate context outside the structured event payload.
  + THEN:
    Emit PSR/PUR as structured event maps with :event, :pattern/id, :session/id, :decision/id; keep annotations in separate fields.
  + BECAUSE:
    Stable schema enables accurate parsing, dedupe, and audit trails.
  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - evidence: sample events include :pattern/selection-claimed and :pattern/use-claimed.
    - evidence-shape: {:event :keyword, :pattern/id :string, :session/id :string, :decision/id :string}
